00:24:01.720 --> 00:24:07.020
And what I have arrived at at the moment, which I'm sure I will disavow in due time,

00:24:07.160 --> 00:24:15.200
is that there is no way for the author's brand not to participate in the text if the author has a public life.

00:24:15.400 --> 00:24:20.380
Or even if that author doesn't, right? Like J.D. Salinger famously did not have a public life.

00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:26.900
But he is all over those books. And, like, when people read them, they read them in the context of J.D. Salinger.

00:24:29.840 --> 00:24:34.300
And I feel like the absolutes in reading texts creates this problem where you're either constantly guessing

00:24:34.320 --> 00:24:41.740
the author's intent, or you're actively trying to divorce yourself everything you know about the world around you and the author.

00:24:42.060 --> 00:24:44.260
